Program: Start the Week
Title: Richard Ford on the US Elections
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01n9wzm
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 15 Oct 2012
On Start the Week Andrew Marr talks to two American authors, Richard Ford and Lionel Shriver about the state of the US. In the run-up to the Presidential elections, the journalist Edward Luce argues that the country's politics are broken, and America is facing the spectre of decline. But the chair of Republicans Abroad UK, Thomas Grant, disputes such a negative assessment. Producer - Katy Hickman. Show less